      "content": "but it doesn't feel like a glitch. it's too consistent. like, every time i listen to a certain type of genre, the hum shifts pitch. it feels intentional, like a signal. if someone actually WAS doing this with sub-audible frequencies to influence mood or stuff, how would they even hide it in a standard stream?",
